  "prompt": "How do I know if he is interested in love or lust?",
  "response": "Determining whether someone is interested in you for love or lust can be challenging, but there are certain signs and behaviors you can look for to help you make that distinction. Here are some key differences to consider:\n\n### Signs of Interest in Love:\n1. **Deep Conversations**: They engage in meaningful conversations and are interested in your thoughts, feelings, and experiences.\n2. **Consistency**: They consistently show interest and make an effort to spend time with you, not just late at night or for physical encounters.\n3. **Respect**: They respect your boundaries and are considerate of your feelings.\n4. **Future Plans**: They talk about future plans that include you and seem genuinely interested in building a life together.\n5. **Emotional Support**: They are there for you during good times and bad, offering emotional support and encouragement.\n6. **Introducing to Friends and Family**: They want to introduce you to their close friends and family members.\n7. **Acts of Kindness**: They show affection through small, thoughtful acts of kindness.\n\n### Signs of Interest in Lust:\n1. **Focus on Physical Appearance**: They frequently comment on your looks or physical attributes rather than your personality or achievements.\n2. **Late-Night Contact**: They mainly contact you late at night or for last-minute plans, often hinting at physical intimacy.\n3. **Avoiding Deep Conversations**: They tend to steer away from deep or meaningful conversations and keep things light and superficial.\n4. **Inconsistent Behavior**: Their interest in you seems to fluctuate and they may disappear for periods of time.\n5. **Lack of Future Plans**: They avoid discussions about the future or any plans that involve commitment.\n6. **Disregard for Boundaries**: They may push for physical intimacy even when you express reluctance or set boundaries.\n7. **Interest in Others**: They may flirt with or show interest in other people openly.\n\n### How to Proceed:\n1. **Communicate**: Open and honest communication is key. Express your feelings and ask about their intentions.\n2. **Observe Actions**: Pay attention to their actions over time, as actions often speak louder than words.\n3. **Set Boundaries**: Clearly define your boundaries and see how they respect them.\n4. **Trust Your Gut**: If something feels off, trust your instincts. Your intuition can be a powerful guide.\n\nUltimately, understanding someone's true intentions can take time. It's important to take things slowly and ensure you feel respected and valued in the relationship.",
